    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-06-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="424" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                <head>No. 395.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Christiancy</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima,
                                Peru</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-06-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 1, 1879</date>. (Received June
                            25.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                        your dispatch No. 11, of the 8th ultimo.</p>
                <p>I am glad to see that the latter substantially approves, in advance, of the
                        views I had expressed to Minister Osborn in mine of the 19th ultimo, of
                        which I sent you a copy in mine of the 20th (No. 15).</p>
                <p>I shall take occasion to communicate to the minister of foreign relations the
                        substance of so much of your dispatch (No. 11) as tends to explain and
                        modify the note of Mr. Gibbs to that minister of April 7th.</p>
                <p>Accept the assurance of the high regard and esteem of your friend,
                        &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>I. P. CHRISTIANCY.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
